# Risk management

Every order — backtest, paper, or live — passes through
`risk.engine.RiskEngine.check_and_size`. There is no bypass flag. Adding
one is a release-blocking review failure.

## Default limits (loaded from `configs/risk.yaml`)

| Limit                     | Default | Checked in                           |
|---------------------------|---------|--------------------------------------|
| Max risk per trade        | 1%      | `risk.sizing.vol_targeted_quantity`  |
| Max daily loss            | 3%      | `risk.engine.RiskEngine`             |
| Max drawdown (peak→trough)| 25%     | `risk.engine.RiskEngine`             |
| Max gross exposure        | 1.0×    | `risk.engine.RiskEngine`             |
| Max leverage              | 1.0×    | `risk.engine.RiskEngine`             |
| Max per-symbol weight     | 25%     | `risk.engine.RiskEngine`             |

Crossing any limit raises `RiskCheckRejected(rule=<name>)`. The rejection
is logged via `monitoring.logger`.

## Required

- Strategy code never sets position sizes. Strategies emit *targets*; the
  risk engine produces *quantities*.
- Live orders carry a `client_order_id` (idempotency).
- The kill-switch (`monitoring.drift.detect_drift`) cancels open orders and
  marks the strategy `retired` when crossed; resuming requires a human.

## Forbidden — CI rejects PRs containing these

- Flags or env vars: `skip_risk`, `bypass_risk`, `RISK_BYPASS`,
  `DISABLE_RISK`, `--no-risk`.
- Direct calls from `strategies/` to `Broker.place_order`.
- LLM-generated trade decisions reaching `execution/` (LLMs are
  research-only; see [`llm-usage.mdc`](mdc:.cursor/rules/llm-usage.mdc)).
- Hardcoded position sizes anywhere.

## Code-review trigger

Any PR touching `risk/`, `execution/`, or `configs/risk.yaml` requires:
human review, a passing `tests/strategy/` + `tests/e2e/` run cited in the
PR description, and a `DECISIONS.md` entry if a default limit changes.

See [`docs/RISK_POLICY.md`](mdc:docs/RISK_POLICY.md) for rationale.
